<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd">
<task id="task_system-config-workflow">
    <title>Configuration Workflow</title>
    <shortdesc>Since some configuration tasks must be completed before others can be performed, use
        this workflow to configure your PHEMI system.</shortdesc>
    <taskbody>
        <steps>
            <stepsection>In these first steps, order matters. You cannot create users until you have
                defined user authorizations. Likewise, you cannot create access policies without
                defining both user authorizations and data visibilities.</stepsection>
            <step>
                <cmd><xref href="../Login/task_logging-on.xml#task_logging-on">Log on to the PHEMI
                        Central Management Console</xref>.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd><xref href="../Users/con_user-authorizations.xml#concept_user-authorizations"
                        >Define user authorizations.</xref></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd><xref href="../Users/task_create-new-user.xml#task_create-new-user">Create
                        users.</xref></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd><xref
                        href="../Data_Visibilities/task_define-data-visibility.xml#task_define-data-visibilities"
                        >Define data visibilities.</xref></cmd>
            </step>
            <stepsection>Data categories must be added before you can define data collections. Access
                policies are optional for data collection configuration. If you are using a Data
                Processing Function (DPF) to create derived data from raw data, you upload the DPF
                archive as part of data collection configuration.</stepsection>
            <step>
                <cmd><xref
                        href="../Data_Categories/task_add-data-category.xml#task_add-data-category"
                        >Add data categories.</xref></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd><xref
                        href="../Access_Policies/task_create-access-policy.xml#task_create-access-policy"
                        >Create access policies.</xref></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd><xref
                        href="../Data_Sources/task_define-data-source.xml#task_define-data-source"
                    >Define data collections.</xref></cmd>
            </step>
            <stepsection>Configuring datasets and dataset destinations is optional.</stepsection>
            <step>
                <cmd><xref href="../Datasets/task_define-dataset.xml#task_define-new-dataset"
                        >Configure datasets.</xref></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd><xref
                        href="../Datasets/task_create-dataset-destination.xml#task_create-dataset-destination"
                        >Configure dataset destinations.</xref></cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
